This is the binary version of the Sather-K compiler for sun4 machines.
For running sck in your local environment you must set two shell variables:

   SATHER_K_HOME : the directory where the sck files are located
   SATHER_K_LIB  : the lib subdirectory of the sck directory

For example in a C-Shell you must do the following:

setenv SATHER_K_HOME __the_sck_directory__
setenv SATHER_K_LIB ${SATHER_K_HOME}/lib
